## Pool Choice: DAMM v2 `initialize_customizable_pool`

Meteora has four pool types. Here is why DAMM v2 with `initialize_customizable_pool`
is the correct one for MoonPad:

**DLMM** — Bin-based concentrated liquidity. Expensive to create (~0.25 SOL per pool
in rent), complex bin management, overkill for a memetoken launch. Skip.

**DAMM v1** — The original constant-product AMM. Fees auto-compound back into the
pool — you cannot claim them separately as SOL. This means you cannot distribute fees
to presale contributors. Skip.

**DBC (Dynamic Bonding Curve)** — Bonding curve from zero supply, not a presale
model. Skip.

**DAMM v2 with `initialize_customizable_pool`** — This is the one:
- Full-range constant-product pool (x·y=k), same pricing model as Uniswap v2 / old Raydium
- LP position is represented as a **position NFT** — whoever holds it can claim trading fees
- `collectFeeMode: 1` (OnlyB) means all LP fees accumulate as SOL only — trivial to distribute
- Supports `permanent_lock_position` which locks the liquidity forever but still allows `claim_fee` from that locked position
- Creates a pool for only ~0.022 SOL in rent vs ~0.5 SOL for Raydium — massively cheaper
- No config key required: pool PDA is just `[tokenAMint, tokenBMint]`
- Immediate trading activation (set `activationPoint = null`)
- Already integrated with Jupiter aggregator for routing

**The key insight on fees:** In DAMM v2, when you permanently lock LP liquidity, you
KEEP the ability to claim trading fees from it. This is unique to Meteora. So MoonPad's
presale contract permanently locks the LP (rug-proof) but can call `claim_fee` on the
position at any time. Those collected SOL fees then get distributed to presale
contributors pro-rata. This is the "LP rewards" feature the user wants.

