## Fee Configuration for Memetokens

Use the anti-sniper fee scheduler. For a memetoken presale, this is ideal:

```
startingFeeBps:  5000   (50% fee at launch — destroys snipers)
endingFeeBps:    100    (1% fee after decay period)
numberOfPeriod:  120    (120 steps)
totalDuration:   7200   (2 hours to decay from 50% → 1%)
feeSchedulerMode: 1     (Exponential decay — drops fast initially, then slows)
dynamicFee:      true   (adds up to 20% of minBaseFeeBps on top during volatility)
collectFeeMode:  1      (OnlyB = SOL fees only — simplest to distribute to contributors)
```

This means:
- First few minutes of trading: ~50% fee — bots and snipers get destroyed
- After 2 hours: settles at 1% base fee + dynamic volatility component
- All fees accumulate as SOL in the position, claimable by the position NFT holder

You can use one of the pre-existing static configs (indices 24-31 in the DAMM v2 docs
have a similar schedule starting at 50% decaying to 2.5%) or configure your own
via `initialize_customizable_pool` which takes inline fee params.

**Recommendation: use `initialize_customizable_pool`** since it does not require a config
key and you control all fee params directly.

