## Updated Fee Economics

With DAMM v2 (vs the original Raydium version):

| Item | Raydium version | Meteora DAMM v2 |
|---|---|---|
| Pool creation cost | ~0.5 SOL | ~0.022 SOL |
| LP burn mechanism | Burn LP tokens | `permanent_lock_position` |
| LP fee recipient | Burned — nobody | Presale contributors (ongoing) |
| Fee claim | N/A | Call `claim_pool_fees` + `collect_my_fees` |
| Fee currency | N/A | SOL (collectFeeMode=1) |
| Anti-sniper fee | None | 50% → 1% exponential decay over 2h |
| Dev launch fee charged | 1 SOL | 1 SOL (now ~0.98 SOL profit margin) |

The key pitch to users: **"Provide liquidity, earn forever."** Presale contributors do
not just get tokens — they get an ongoing share of every trade that happens on the
token, paid out in SOL. This is a fundamentally more attractive product than Pinksale
or other launchpads that simply burn LP.

